    <solution><p>To solve <m>45x^{16}-5x^{14} = 0 \text{,}</m> we can factor out the GCF, <m>5x^{14}\text{.}</m> Thus, the equation becomes <m>5x^{14}(9x^{2}-1)=0\text{.}</m> Keep solving this by setting each factor equal to zero.</p>
